newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline weaker with futures, market tight.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline weaker with futures, market tight.

text.p: NWE gasoline was weak on Wednesday as NYMEX futures fell but the market was tight, traders said.
Eurograde barges traded at $204 fob ARA but activity was thin. September swaps traded at a $9 backwardation to October.

The sale of 40,000 tonnes of regular unleaded gasoline and 20,000 tonnes of premium to the U.S. on Monday further tightened the market. The regular was heard sold at 7.2 cents under October NYMEX, while the Eurograde went at October -4 cents.
A 12,000 tonne MTBE cargo was sold from Fos on Tuesday to a trader at a p+c quotes-related price. It is expected to move to Canada.-- Nicholas Shaxson, London newsroom +44 171 542 8167
